      "id": 336313,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The reaction of hydroxide ion with chloromethane to yield methanol and chloride ion is an example of a general reaction type called a nucleophilic substitution reaction:</p>\n<p></p>HO<sup>−</sup> + CH<sub>3</sub>Cl ⇄ CH<sub>3</sub>OH + Cl<sup>−</sup><p></p>\n<p>The value of Δ<i>H</i>° for the reaction is −75 kJ/mol, and the value of Δ<i>S</i>° is +54 J/(K·mol). What is the value of Δ<i>G</i>° (in kJ/mol) at 298 K? Is the reaction exothermic or endothermic? Is it exergonic or endergonic?</p>",
